HEADWORD: Groats
<hw>Groats</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>grot</ets>, AS. <ets>gr⟦amac⟧tan</ets>; akin to Icel.
<ets>grautr</ets> porridge, and to E. <ets>gritt</ets>,
<ets>grout</ets>. See <er>Grout</er>.]</ety> <def>Dried grain, as oats
or wheat, hulled and broken or crushed; in high milling, cracked
fragments of wheat larger than grits.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Embden groats</b></col>, <cd>crushed oats.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

